                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d205">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">500.C001/821a: Circular telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bingham</hi>
                    </persName>)<note n="72" xml:id="d205fn72">The same, <hi rend="italic">mutatis
                            mutandis</hi>, October 14, to the American diplomatic missions in
                        France, Italy, Czechoslovakia, and Poland.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-10-14T10:00:00-05:00"
                            >October 14, 1933—10 a.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>As soon as you are able to determine the attitude of the British Government
                    toward the reported German withdrawal from the League of Nations and the
                    Disarmament Conference and its implications, please telegraph a full
                    analysis.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
